{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784315299118115002,"compiled_state":{"alias":"heated-chattable-waterbug","assignee":null,"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":2,"unsigned":0},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"f387d8680dee94872ad0aecd29558d90a2876b23d232efc6ab5c4fd32cc93991","event_uuid":"1929ecec-ec76-4211-8f2b-8ee880785dbd","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784315279846245001-1929ecec-ec76-4211-8f2b-8ee880785dbd"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"e046abb43078df6faea9f1204a4cfc2bf317dcfbecd9c5afbe791baf644a6b05","event_uuid":"b4894146-3cdc-4189-a5c5-52738af4657a","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784315299118115001-b4894146-3cdc-4189-a5c5-52738af4657a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[],"created_at":1784315279846245001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"b4894146-3cdc-4189-a5c5-52738af4657a","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"5dac-c177-56ff-4af4"}],"description":"# Durable write path drops concurrent locked writes: background git auto-gc races the object DB\n\n## Summary\nUnder heavy concurrent write load, the rebar durable write path (`event_append`) loses\ncommitted writes. Writers holding the exclusive index lock fail their `git commit` with\n`error: invalid object <sha> for '<...>.json' ... error: Error building trees` and the\nwrite is silently dropped. The regression test\n`tests/interfaces/store/test_enrich_drain_prune_concurrency.py::test_enrich_queue_prune_never_drops_concurrent_locked_writes`\ncatches it (e.g. `intended=250 persisted_on_disk=233 lost=17`), and it is **currently red on\n`main` repo-wide** — it fails ~9 of the last ~12 `main` post-merge CI runs, including the CI\nrun of the very commit that tried to fix it (`485873652`, post-merge run `29593239791`,\n`lost=17`). Because it fails Verified on unrelated changes, it is friction on every Gerrit\nlanding (mitigated today only by probabilistic `recheck`).\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run the integration tier under parallel xdist load, e.g.\n   `.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/interfaces/store/test_enrich_drain_prune_concurrency.py -q`\n   repeatedly, or observe `main`'s post-merge `test` workflow across several pushes.\n2. The test spawns `_WRITERS=5` writers × `_BURSTS=25` (`intended=250`) concurrent\n   lock-serialized writes while the enrich-queue prune runs.\n3. Intermittently (load-dependent), some writes raise the `invalid object / Error building\n   trees` `CommandError` while holding the lock and are swallowed → `lost>0`.\n\n**Expected:** every lock-acquiring write persists to disk; `swallowed_write_raises == 0` and\n`persisted_on_disk == intended_total`.\n**Actual:** under load a fraction of writes are lost (observed losses 17/26/94/146 across\nruns/workers — the varying count is itself a signature of a load-dependent race).\n\n## Root Cause (diagnosed)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/init.py` (~L96–117) deliberately re-enabled **stock git background gc**\n  on the tracker repo — `--unset gc.auto` + `gc.autoDetach=true` (commit `f63d72662`,\n  \"WU-1 — re-enable stock git gc (drop gc.auto=0 forcing)\", 2026-06-18).\n- Under this test's heavy parallel commit load the loose-object count crosses git's `gc.auto`\n  threshold; git forks a **detached background `gc --auto`** that repacks/prunes loose objects\n  **concurrently with the writers** — an object can vanish between `git add` and `git commit`.\n- `485873652` added `_recover_from_invalid_object` (Mode D, `event_append.py:713`): on an\n  `invalid object / error building trees` commit failure it runs `git read-tree HEAD`, re-adds\n  the current write's path, and retries. This reduced the damage ~6–8× (146 → ~17) but does\n  **not** cover the case where the missing object is **reachable from HEAD** (a committed\n  object caught by the background repack): `read-tree HEAD` reinstates the broken reference, the\n  retry commit fails identically, and the recovery is one-shot (no bounded loop / escalation).\n  The failing logs show the **same object sha for the same path cascading across sequential\n  bursts**, which is the HEAD-reachable signature.\n\n## Fix Direction (candidate; needs maintainer judgment on the gc trade-off)\n1. **Neutralize the trigger on the durable write path:** force `gc.auto=0` (or at minimum\n   `gc.autoDetach=false`) on the tracker repo so a background repack cannot run concurrently\n   with commits. This revisits the deliberate `f63d72662` decision — understand *why* WU-1\n   re-enabled gc (loose-object growth? perf?) before reverting; a scoped\n   \"no auto-gc while the exclusive write lock is held\" is preferable to a blanket revert.\n2. **Harden the recovery to the HEAD-reachable case:** after `read-tree HEAD`, if the missing\n   object is still referenced from HEAD, regenerate it from the intact worktree file\n   (re-`git add` the committed path from disk) before retry; make `_recover_from_invalid_object`\n   a **bounded loop** rather than one-shot.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Root cause confirmed: a targeted repro demonstrates a background `gc --auto` (or manual\n      `git gc` under load) is what prunes the object referenced by the failing commit.\n- [ ] The durable write path no longer loses writes under the test's load: \n      `test_enrich_queue_prune_never_drops_concurrent_locked_writes` passes **50/50 consecutive\n      runs locally** under xdist parallelism (currently flakes).\n- [ ] `main` post-merge CI passes this test across **10 consecutive** pushes after the fix lands\n      (was failing ~9/12).\n- [ ] The chosen gc trade-off is documented (a code comment + the ticket) explaining the\n      interaction between WU-1's gc re-enablement and the write path, so it is not silently\n      re-reverted.\n- [ ] No regression in the durable-write / enrich-drain unit + integration tiers\n      (`make test` green).\n\n## Notes / Provenance\nDiscovered while landing epic 6982's R6 change (`5dac`, Gerrit #760): #760 touches nothing in\n`src/rebar/_store/*` yet failed this test on CI, while sibling #761 (superset runtime tree)\npassed — i.e. a probabilistic store-layer race, not a defect in the plan-review changes. Full\ndiagnosis captured here so a maintainer can pick it up; not in epic 6982's plan-review scope.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"open","tags":[],"ticket_id":"bfe1-309d-6e86-4749","ticket_type":"bug","title":"Durable write path drops concurrent locked writes: background git auto-gc races object DB","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["1929ecec-ec76-4211-8f2b-8ee880785dbd","b4894146-3cdc-4189-a5c5-52738af4657a"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784315299118115002,"uuid":"02f501fc-e146-4fe8-940a-53aac4194f4c"}